Gov. Oluwarotimi Akeredolu of Ondo State on Wednesday approved the appointment of Mrs Margaret Atere as his Senior Special Assistant on Women Affairs. Mr Olusegun Ajiboye, Chief Press Secretary to the governor, in a statement in Akure, said the appointment was with immediate effect. “Akeredolu congratulates the appointee as she joins the governor to further push forward efforts aimed at developing the state,” he said. Vanguard Gov. Oluwarotimi Akeredolu of Ondo State has pledged more women friendly programmes and policies to guarantee equal right in all spheres of life to reduce gender barriers facing women in the state. March 8, 2018 In "News" Gov. Oluwarotimi Akeredolu of Ondo State, on Tuesday, approved the appointments of seven Senior Special Assistants (SSA). April 18, 2017 In "News" Ondo State Governor, Oluwarotimi Akeredolu, on Monday approved the appointment of Mr. Gani Mohammed as his Senior Special Assistant (SSA) on New Media. The Chief Press Secretary to the governor, Mr. Segun Ajiboye, disclosed this in a statement in Akure, the state capital. Ajiboye said Akeredolu also approved the appointment… September 23, 2019 In "News"